  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      There is a gating mechanism in the dorsal horn of the spinal cord that acts to facilitate or
      inhibit transmission of pain signals to the brain. The gate can be closed by mechanical
      stimuli such as touch and vibration.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The researcher develope a device that can use to reduce pain during drug administration or
      blood collection with needles.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
